Answer:
\section{n}
wake nob perish kangaroo wake unique monkey idiot vigor lamb groot qualify

examples.Question: What is the content of 2th subsection under 1th section? The content should be an excerpt as it appears in the LaTeX file, including the heading line and any sub-section.
examples.Answer:
\section{n}
banana kangaroo nob oops banana idiot essence cafe X-ray ravish cafe dentist

RuleHint: Note that section title is enclosed by \\section{}, and \\subsection for subsection, \\subsubsection for subsubsection. To find the content of certain section, look for ith section as specified, and start from there look for jth subsection. And from located subsection, look for kth subsubsection as queried. Search may stop early if subsection or subsubsection is not queried.
